SIMPLE: shirt_waist
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shirt waist
<hw>Shirt waist</hw></mhw>.
<ety>[<ets>shirt</ets> + <ets>waist</ets>; see <er>waist{3}</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A woman's blouse resembling a
men's shirt in cut and style; -- in England called a
<altname>blouse</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a type of woman's dress with a bodice tailored like
a shirt; -- also called <altname>shirt dress</altname>,
<altname>shirtwaist dress</altname>, and
<altname>shirtwaister</altname>.</def> <au>[RHUD]</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shirt-waist suit</ent>⟦br⟧
